  "doc_id": "22297",
  "text": "The continual reassessment method was used to allocate doses. [CITATION_1] A design with grouped inclusions of three patients per dose level was chosen, with lenalidomide 10 mg/day as a starting dose to be administered to the first cohort. DLT probabilities at all dose levels were updated using Bayes' theorem. The process was repeated until a fixed sample size (n=24) was reached or a stopping criterion was fulfilled [CITATION_2] using Bayesian Phase I Dose-Ranging software. [CITATION_3] More details are reported in the Online Supplementary Material.",
